Introduction
Programming is like magic for computers, and JavaScript is its popular language for creating interactive websites. With JavaScript, we bring web pages to life with animations, user interactions, and real-time updates, making the internet dynamic and fun for all!
Focus: Getting Started with Programming, Introduction to JavaScript and JavaScript Operators
Prerequisites: VS Code IDE with Node.js installed
Theme
Imagine you're a freelance Web developer with a new client who requires a website that is both visually appealing and functional. To meet their expectations, you must have a solid foundation in JavaScript programming, enabling you to create dynamic user interfaces, handle user input, and manipulate data to make the site come alive.
Learning the basics of JavaScript programming can enhance your web development skills significantly. You'll be able to create captivating and interactive websites that attract users and keep them coming back for more. So, let's delve into the world of JavaScript programming and discover how it can revolutionize how you build websites! 
Primary Goals
Understand the basics of programming, such as variables, control flow, and functions.
Understand the syntax and structure of the JavaScript language
Learn about the different types of operators in JavaScript.
Learn how to set up a development environment to write and test JavaScript code.
Chapter Essentials
Learning Lessons
The chapter comprises multiple lessons that center around Programming Basics, Introduction to JavaScript, and JavaScript Operators.
The lesson consists of learning material and engaging activities that enhance the learner's experience.
Lessons conclude with coding questions to practice various coding concepts in IDE. Solving the coding problems will enhance understanding and proficiency in the taught technologies.
In addition, every lesson includes 10 MCQs aimed at enhancing knowledge.
Skill Mastery Challenge
The chapter includes a Skill Mastery Challenge with a Summary section for the given chapter for best practices, challenges, and additional references, an Interview Prep section with industry-specific concepts, and a Competency Challenge featuring a one-hour session with 40 MCQs for reinforced learning and identifying improvement areas.
Earning the Competency Challenge Certificate will ensure the completion of this chapter.
